1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 { D00 Queen's Pawn Game: Mason Attack } 2... e6 3. e3 e5 { 900 player notices one move threats. } 4. Bxe5 Bb4+ 5. c3 Be7 6. Nf3 { 900 player systematically develops pieces. } 6... f6 7. Bf4 Bg4 8. Bb5+ Kf8 9. Nbd2 c6 10. Bd3 b6 11. O-O f5 12. c4 g5 13. Be5 Nd7 14. Bxh8 c5 15. cxd5 f4 16. Qc1 fxe3 17. fxe3 { Notice that the 900's playbook is working beautifully. He makes a threat, and then captures a piece. } 17... cxd4 18. Bxd4 Bb4 19. a3 Rc8 20. Nc4 Nc5 21. Nfe5+ Nf6 22. Bg6 Qxd5 23. Rxf6+ Ke7 24. Qf1 Rg8 25. Bxh7 Ne4 26. Rf7+ Ke8 27. Nxg4 Qd8 28. Bxg8 Bd2 29. Nxd2 Nxd2 30. Qb5+ { Black resigns. } 1-0


