{ The 900 player runs his playbook, but it fails for the first time. }
1. d4 g6 2. e4 Bg7 3. Nf3 d6 4. Be2 Nf6 5. Nc3 { B08 Pirc Defense: Classical Variation, Quiet System } { The 900 player is being exposed to opening theory from his opponent. } 5... O-O 6. O-O Nbd7 7. e5 { The 950 player has no idea that he is following Rozentalis - Svidler 1995. He has managed some opening theory by following his play book. Develop - Make threat - Take pieces - Win. } { [%cal Ge5f6] } 7... dxe5 8. dxe5 Ng4 9. Nd4? { (0.79 → -0.51) Mistake. Best move was e6. } (9. e6 Nde5 10. exf7+ Nxf7 11. Qxd8 Rxd8 12. Bc4 Kf8 13. Re1 Nge5 14. Nxe5 Nxe5 15. Bb3 Bf5) 9... Ndxe5 10. Bxg4? { (-0.65 → -2.00) Mistake. Best move was Bf4. } (10. Bf4 Nh6) 10... Nxg4? { (-2.00 → -0.97) Mistake. Best move was Bxg4. } (10... Bxg4) 11. f3?? { (-0.97 → -6.65) Blunder. Best move was Nf3. } { Note the tactical win for black on the board. Remember for 1300 stuff. } (11. Nf3) 11... Nh6?? { (-6.65 → -1.65) Blunder. Best move was Qxd4+. } (11... Qxd4+ 12. Qxd4) 12. Ncb5?? { (-1.65 → -5.18) Blunder. Best move was Nb3. } { [%csl Gc7] } (12. Nb3 b6) 12... c6 13. Bxh6?! { (-4.98 → -5.48) Inaccuracy. Best move was c3. } (13. c3 cxb5) 13... Bxh6 14. Na3?! { (-5.44 → -6.15) Inaccuracy. Best move was Qe2. } (14. Qe2 cxb5) 14... Be3+ 15. Kh1 Bxd4 16. c3 Bg7 17. Qxd8 Rxd8 18. g4 Be6 19. Rae1? { (-6.72 → -7.72) Mistake. Best move was Rf2. } (19. Rf2 Rd3 20. Nc2 Rad8 21. Kg2 Bf6 22. Nd4 Bxd4 23. cxd4 R8xd4 24. Re1 Kg7 25. b3 h5) 19... Rd6?! { (-7.72 → -6.73) Inaccuracy. Best move was Rd2. } (19... Rd2) 20. c4? { (-6.73 → -7.83) Mistake. Best move was Re2. } (20. Re2 Bf6 21. b3 Bxc3 22. Kg2 Rad8 23. h3 Bb4 24. Nc4 Bxc4 25. bxc4 a5 26. Rb2 Rd2+) 20... Bxb2 21. Rb1? { (-7.91 → -11.89) Mistake. Best move was Nc2. } (21. Nc2 Bxc4 22. Rf2 Bf6 23. Ne3 Be6 24. Rc2 Rd3 25. Kg2 Bg5 26. Nc4 Bd5 27. Ne5 Ra3) 21... Bxa3 22. Rxb7 Rd7 23. Rb3 Bxc4 24. Rfb1 Bxb3 25. Rxb3 Rd1+ 26. Kg2 Rd2+ 27. Kg3 Rxa2 28. Kh4 Rxh2+ 29. Kg3 Bd6+ 30. f4 Rh1 31. Rc3 c5 32. g5 Rg1+ 33. Kf3 a5 34. Kf2?! { (-23.77 → Mate in 16) Checkmate is now unavoidable. Best move was Ke2. } (34. Ke2 Rg4 35. Kf1 Rxf4+ 36. Ke2 a4 37. Ra3 Rb4 38. Kd1 Rb2 39. Rd3 Rg2 40. Rf3 Rxg5) 34... Rb1 35. Ke3?! { (-54.90 → Mate in 11) Checkmate is now unavoidable. Best move was f5. } (35. f5 gxf5) 35... a4 36. Ke4 a3 37. f5 a2 38. f6 exf6 39. gxf6 a1=Q 40. Rd3 Ra4+?! { (Mate in 4 → Mate in 4) Not the best checkmate sequence. Best move was Qe5+. } (40... Qe5+ 41. Kf3 Qf4+ 42. Ke2 Ra2+ 43. Rd2 Rxd2#) 41. Kd5 Rd4+?! { (Mate in 2 → Mate in 4) Not the best checkmate sequence. Best move was Rb6. } (41... Rb6 42. Rd2 Qe5#) 42. Rxd4 Qxd4+ { White resigns. } 0-1


