{ Opening - Expose to minor amounts of theory. Give them just enough to get their pieces developed - no tactical memorization - only opening traps from a defensive point of view!!

Middle Game - Expose to basic tactics, pin fork skewer, double attack, etc. This can be done through programs like CT-ART and ChessBase. Push them to better visual memory - Make them calculate several moves ahead in forced lines. Teach materialism in regard to trading pieces or not trading pieces.

End Game - Basic Mates - K+R, K+Q, Begin teaching pawn endings at a very basic level. Concepts like opposition and the square of the pawn are fundamentals that should be absorbed here. }
1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. d3 (4. Ng5) *


